<br />
<br><br />
Ok, the Idea of this deck is simple. Get out Aragorn with the Pony, make him and Boromir no stranger to the shadows, and have frodo and merry bust out their talent for not being seen. If you have their fellowship under control, try moving twice if you think you can, espically if it is to a sanctuary. hobbit stealth everything you can, but if its easy going, save them for site 5 because of problems like cheaper uruk-hai and more than 1 nazgul. basically just play smart, some combos will be shown below.<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
ARV + Elendil&#39;s Valor = Boromir can hold off a few guys, and use his sword to kill off one or two of em, and still win. Valor can be used on its own, usually best later in game, just to have boromir hold off a few guys.<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
instead of regular aimed archery, this deck runs allied aimed archery. works vs everything but nazgul, and in that case aragorns bow works well, if its out. Galadriel comes down, then exerts to make everyone else free, as well as to heal them. Celeborn is there to heal in emergencies, and to get extra cards with elrond.<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
everything else in the free peoples is self explanatory... dmail me if you cant figure it out<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
as for shadow, this is my modified verson of whispers of errata. i added in some under the watching eyes, upped it to four morgul skulkers, put in some nazgul swords, and just made it what i thought was better for my current meta situation. if you didnt read that deck, basically just play the sauron minions to exert and play the nice conditions to burden frodo up real nicely (and with skulkers to recycle nazgul cards) then use dark whispers, swords, and threshold to make the nazgul insane, and kill off the fellowship. kinda intensive, and doesnt work well vs gandalf, but if it does work, its great. even vs gandalf you can generally get a few burdens on frodo before they can find a sleep.<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
